<TITLE> Dhaka Phone chairman again refused bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 24 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court has for a second time rejected bail applications made by two Dhaka Phone top executives in a case alleging their involvement in illegal VoIP operations. Dhaka's metropolitan sessions judge ANM Bashirullah refused the applications made by the company's chairman Hayatuzzaman and director KM Shahidullah on Wednesday. The Chief Metropolitan Magistrate's Court had on Mar 15 refused the two men bail when he sent them to jail. Five top officials of Dhaka Phone were arrested on Mar 14 following a raid on its Mahakhali office where Bangladesh Telecommunications Regulatory Commission (BTRC) officials claim they found evidence of illegal Voice over Internet Protocol (VoIP) operations. The court sent the company's chairman and Director to jail the following day and ordered the police to question three others, the director general (engineering) Harun-al-Atahar, senior manager (engineering) Ikramuzzaman and the manager (billing) Hari Podder, at the jail gate. A case had been filed on December 24 last year with Badda Police Station against the Dhaka Phone officials for the illegal connection of foreign calls. Banned equipment was also seized at that time. The BTRC allege that although the company officials were warned at that time, they have again started operating illegal VoIP services. The five detainees were shown arrested in connection with last year's 
